# A Time of War Companion - First Printing Corrected with Errata v1.1
Rank - Expanded Rules;RANK (EXPANDED) [CHARACTER (IDENTITY)]<br>Optional Companion rules expand the core Rank trait with faction-specific military rank structures, rank equivalencies, and command authority notes. Use the core Rank trait for XP spending; use this entry as the Companion reference for advanced campaign handling. See Companion p.29.
Title/Bloodname - Expanded Rules;TITLE/BLOODNAME (EXPANDED) [CHARACTER (IDENTITY)]<br>Optional Companion rules expand the core Title/Bloodname trait with affiliation-specific titles, Bloodname context, and rank-to-title equivalency guidance. Use the core Title/Bloodname trait for XP spending; use this entry as the Companion reference for advanced campaign handling. See Companion p.42.
Vehicle - Expanded Rules;VEHICLE (EXPANDED) [VEHICLE]<br>Optional Companion rules expand the core Vehicle trait with pilot certification, replacement, lien, and superheavy-unit guidance. Use the core Vehicle trait for XP spending; use this entry as the Companion reference for advanced campaign handling. See Companion p.49.
Custom Vehicle - Expanded Rules;CUSTOM VEHICLE (EXPANDED) [VEHICLE]<br>Optional Companion rules expand the core Custom Vehicle trait with equipment-rating and maintenance-quality guidance for more detailed vehicle selection. Use the core Custom Vehicle trait for XP spending; use this entry as the Companion reference for advanced campaign handling. See Companion p.49.
Implant/Prosthetic - Expanded Rules;IMPLANT/PROSTHETIC (EXPANDED) [CHARACTER]<br>Optional Companion rules expand the core Implant/Prosthetic trait with advanced implant, cybernetic, prosthetic, and genetic-modification type guidance. Use the core Implant/Prosthetic trait for XP spending; use this entry as the Companion reference for advanced campaign handling. See Companion p.51.
Mutation;MUTATION [CHARACTER]<br>Trait Type [TP Score]: Variable, Multiple [-5 to +3 TP]<br>A Companion trait for unusual genetic conditions, environmental adaptations, or deliberate genetic modifications not cleanly covered by existing core traits. Player and gamemaster should agree on the mutation's cause, visibility, drawbacks, and benefits. See Companion p.55.
